---
// Figure: Holder choice inside a trust model
// State authority issues. Multiple certified holder surfaces present.
// One trust framework. Preserved semantics (disclosure rules, status meanings,
// trust bindings) across every certified holder — plurality is compatible with
// authority only when semantics remain intact.
// Static SVG, standards-note tone.
---

<div class="reveal my-12 md:my-16">
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border overflow-hidden" style="background: rgba(11,11,17,0.6);">
    <div class="p-6 md:p-8">

      <div class="mb-6">
        <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-1">Trust architecture</p>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-bold text-lg tracking-tight">Holder choice inside a trust model</h3>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1.45fr,1fr] gap-5 md:gap-6">

        <!-- SVG -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border/60 p-3 md:p-4" style="background: rgba(11,11,17,0.4);">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 600 470" class="w-full" role="img" aria-label="Diagram with the state as authoritative issuer at the top, a single trust framework band in the middle, and multiple certified holder surfaces below. Preserved semantics — disclosure rules, status meanings, trust bindings — flow across all holders.">
            <defs>
              <marker id="hctm-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="rgba(167,139,250,0.7)"/>
              </marker>
            </defs>

            <!-- Issuer -->
            <rect x="210" y="20" width="180" height="54" rx="8" fill="rgba(167,139,250,0.1)" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.6)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="300" y="43" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="13" font-weight="600">State as issuer</text>
            <text x="300" y="60" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">authoritative source of claims</text>

            <!-- Arrow into trust framework -->
            <line x1="300" y1="74" x2="300" y2="110" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.45)" stroke-width="1.2" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>

            <!-- Trust framework band -->
            <rect x="40" y="115" width="520" height="90" rx="10" fill="rgba(167,139,250,0.06)" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.45)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="300" y="138" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(167,139,250,0.85)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="10" font-weight="600" letter-spacing="2">TRUST FRAMEWORK · ONE</text>
            <text x="300" y="158" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.85)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="12" font-weight="600">Certification · register · specific agreements</text>

            <!-- Preserved semantics line inside trust band -->
            <line x1="75" y1="180" x2="525" y2="180" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.3)" stroke-dasharray="3 3" stroke-width="1"/>
            <text x="300" y="196" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.65)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10" font-style="italic">
              preserved across every certified holder
            </text>

            <!-- Semantic tags -->
            <g font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9" fill="rgba(167,139,250,0.75)">
              <text x="90" y="176">disclosure rules</text>
              <text x="230" y="176">status meanings</text>
              <text x="378" y="176">trust bindings</text>
              <text x="490" y="176">audit</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Arrows down from framework to holders -->
            <line x1="140" y1="205" x2="140" y2="240" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.4)" stroke-width="1.2" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>
            <line x1="300" y1="205" x2="300" y2="240" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.4)" stroke-width="1.2" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>
            <line x1="460" y1="205" x2="460" y2="240" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.4)" stroke-width="1.2" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>

            <!-- Certified holders row -->
            <g>
              <rect x="55" y="245" width="170" height="88" rx="10" fill="rgba(56,189,248,0.06)" stroke="rgba(56,189,248,0.5)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
              <text x="140" y="268" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="12" font-weight="600">GOV.UK Wallet</text>
              <text x="140" y="284" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">first-party holder</text>
              <line x1="75" y1="298" x2="205" y2="298" stroke="rgba(56,189,248,0.2)" stroke-width="0.8"/>
              <text x="140" y="313" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(56,189,248,0.75)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9">same disclosure rules</text>
              <text x="140" y="326" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(56,189,248,0.75)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9">same status semantics</text>
            </g>

            <g>
              <rect x="215" y="245" width="170" height="88" rx="10" fill="rgba(74,222,128,0.06)" stroke="rgba(74,222,128,0.5)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
              <text x="300" y="268" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="12" font-weight="600">Third-party holder</text>
              <text x="300" y="284" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">certified alternative wallet</text>
              <line x1="235" y1="298" x2="365" y2="298" stroke="rgba(74,222,128,0.2)" stroke-width="0.8"/>
              <text x="300" y="313" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(74,222,128,0.75)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9">same disclosure rules</text>
              <text x="300" y="326" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(74,222,128,0.75)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9">same status semantics</text>
            </g>

            <g>
              <rect x="375" y="245" width="170" height="88" rx="10" fill="rgba(34,211,238,0.06)" stroke="rgba(34,211,238,0.5)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
              <text x="460" y="268" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="12" font-weight="600">Sector holder</text>
              <text x="460" y="284" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">e.g. bank · telco · employer</text>
              <line x1="395" y1="298" x2="525" y2="298" stroke="rgba(34,211,238,0.2)" stroke-width="0.8"/>
              <text x="460" y="313" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(34,211,238,0.75)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9">same disclosure rules</text>
              <text x="460" y="326" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(34,211,238,0.75)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="9">same status semantics</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Downstream: checkers and relying parties -->
            <line x1="140" y1="333" x2="140" y2="360" stroke="rgba(232,232,240,0.3)" stroke-width="1" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>
            <line x1="300" y1="333" x2="300" y2="360" stroke="rgba(232,232,240,0.3)" stroke-width="1" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>
            <line x1="460" y1="333" x2="460" y2="360" stroke="rgba(232,232,240,0.3)" stroke-width="1" marker-end="url(#hctm-arrow)"/>

            <rect x="40" y="365" width="520" height="56" rx="10" fill="rgba(245,158,11,0.05)" stroke="rgba(245,158,11,0.4)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="300" y="388" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.85)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="12" font-weight="600">Checkers and relying parties see the same trust semantics from every holder</text>
            <text x="300" y="406" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">the relying party does not need to know which holder was used</text>

            <!-- Failure arrow: semantic drift -->
            <text x="300" y="450" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(239,68,68,0.8)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="10">
              failure mode: a certified holder quietly relaxes a boundary — relying party cannot tell
            </text>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <!-- Preserved semantics panel -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border/60 p-4 md:p-5" style="background: rgba(11,11,17,0.4);">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-text-tertiary mb-4">
            Preserved across every certified holder
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm">
            <li>
              <p class="text-text-secondary font-display font-semibold text-xs tracking-wide mb-1">Disclosure rules</p>
              <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs leading-relaxed">Selective disclosure is enforced the same way on every holder. No certified wallet may widen what is revealed.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="text-text-secondary font-display font-semibold text-xs tracking-wide mb-1">Status meanings</p>
              <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs leading-relaxed">Active, suspended, revoked, expired, deleted mean the same thing on every holder. No local reinterpretation.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="text-text-secondary font-display font-semibold text-xs tracking-wide mb-1">Trust bindings</p>
              <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs leading-relaxed">The same issuer signatures, key rotation rules, and status endpoints bind every holder to the same authority.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="text-text-secondary font-display font-semibold text-xs tracking-wide mb-1">Audit surface</p>
              <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs leading-relaxed">Every certified holder is inspectable under the same rules. Certification is ongoing, not a one-time stamp.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="mt-5 pt-4 border-t border-border/40">
            <p class="text-[10px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-text-tertiary mb-2">Plurality works only when</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              All four of the above are identical across every certified holder. If one holder drifts, authority fragments and the relying party has no way to tell.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs mt-3 text-center italic">
    Authority to issue does not require a monopoly on presentation. Plurality is compatible with authority only when disclosure rules, status meanings, and trust bindings remain intact across every certified holder.
  </p>
</div>
